## üîë Key Principles

### Focus is a Competitive Advantage

- **Good products**: Do one thing exceptionally well
- **Bad products**: Do many things adequately
- **Klick's thing**: Teach composition through real-time feedback

### When to Say No

**Say NO to**:
- Features that don't teach composition
- Features users can get elsewhere
- Features that dilute brand identity
- Features not on roadmap without strong justification

**Say YES to**:
- Composition techniques (core mission)
- Learning experience improvements
- Performance optimizations
- Better feedback mechanisms

### The "Hotdog Test"

**Question**: "Does this feature pass the hotdog test?"

**If someone asks**: "Why does a composition camera app detect hotdogs?"
**And you can't give a compelling composition-teaching answer**
**Then**: Feature fails, reject immediately

---

**Remember**: Every feature has a cost. Every addition is a commitment. Every "yes" is a hundred "no's". Stay focused on teaching composition.

**Default Answer**: NO

**Right Answer**: "Does it teach composition?"
